  unreadable binary files (DOCX and PDF) into text format for further
  integration.
overview: "The user wanted to consolidate various original communication
  documents related to a sleep questionnaire application into a structured set
  of requirements and specifications. The agent began by identifying existing
  documents, including an outline, email instructions, a Word document, and a
  PDF. Recognizing the binary nature of the Word and PDF files, the agent
  initially moved them to a correspondence directory along with other source
  documents. When the user explicitly requested conversion of these unreadable
  formats, the agent successfully used textutil for the DOCX and pdftotext for
  the PDF, converting them into text files. The agent then created two main
  documents: REQUIREMENTS.md for high-level requirements and a validation
  checklist, and QUESTIONNAIRE_SPEC.md for detailed question structure, scoring
  logic, and diagnostic criteria. The original binary files were removed after
  successful conversion, and the conversation concluded with the agent preparing
  to integrate the newly extracted content into the main requirements
  documents."
